\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 50. R. illyricus }L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 552 (1753) ({\i R. scythicus} Klokov) Appressed-sericeous perennial up to c. 50 cm, with ovoid tubers. Basal leaves 3-fid; segments linear-lanceolate, entire or 2- or 3-fid into linear-lanceolate, entire lobes. Receptacle glabrous. Achenes c. 3 mm, more or less triangular, strongly compressed and almost winged, finely punctate; beak about as long as achene, nearly straight. 2n = 32.{\i  Dry grassland; calcicole. C. & S.E. Europe extending to Italy; Öland.} Au Bu Cz Ge Gr Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs(C, W, K, E) Su Tu.
