\pard\f0\fs28 Plants from S. Ukraine, like {\b 51} but with basal leaves palmatisect and with narrowly linear segments have been called{\b  R. odessanus} Klokov fil., {\i Nov. Syst. Pl. Varc.} ({\i Leningrad}){\b  1968}: 120 (1968), and plants from E. Ukraine and S. Russia, like {\b 51} but with stems more pubescent, basal leaves with fewer, wider segments, larger flowers and subglabrous (not densely hairy) sepals have been called{\b  R. silvisteppaceus} Dubovik,{\i  op. cit.} 116 (1968); their status is uncertain.
